        "cat_hj1": { "type": "category", "settings": { "heading": "Hip & Joint" } },
        "faq_hj1": { "type": "item", "settings": { "heading": "How long until I see improvement in my dog's mobility?", "content": "<p>Many pet parents notice improvements in mobility and comfort within 4-8 weeks of consistent daily use. Senior dogs or those with advanced joint issues may take longer to show significant improvement.</p>" } },
        "faq_hj2": { "type": "item", "settings": { "heading": "Is this safe for dogs already on joint medication?", "content": "<p>Please consult your veterinarian if your dog is taking prescription joint medications. Natural supplements can often complement prescribed treatments safely, but your vet should confirm for your specific dog.</p>" } },
        "faq_hj3": { "type": "item", "settings": { "heading": "What breeds benefit most?", "content": "<p>While any dog can benefit, breeds prone to joint issues - like German Shepherds, Golden Retrievers, Labradors, and large/giant breeds - tend to see the most significant improvements in mobility and comfort.</p>" } },
        "faq_hj4": { "type": "item", "settings": { "heading": "Can younger dogs take Hip & Joint as prevention?", "content": "<p>Yes! Starting joint support early is a great proactive strategy, especially for large breeds. Prevention is always easier than treatment, and our formula is safe for ongoing daily use.</p>" } }
      },
